description: Well, given the Corona Virus pandemic and all, and since I am stuck in the house for a while, I had some time to put this together. This interview was conducted live on KPCC FM 89.3 back in 1996. Louie Bellson was in town to play some shows at The Jazz Bakery in Culver City plus he had a new CD out. So we killed two birds with one stone and promoted everything. This was a short visit but a real good one. It makes for a great listen and is quite informative. I forgot how much fun I had doing these on live radio. A lucky man am I! Enjoy all of my drummer friends! There will be more coming as I rip through the boxes of tapes from the 80's and 90's. Peace.
